    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in true showroom condition. This specimen features the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine with its sequential twin-turbocharger system fully intact and operating with perfect transition timing. Compression testing shows exceptional, uniform PSI across all rotor faces, confirming the health of the apex seals. The chassis remains structurally flawless, retaining its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential. Gear engagement through the five-speed manual transmission is tight and precise, with no synchro wear. This is a rare, unmolested example with a pristine undercarriage and zero thermal degradation in the engine bay, representing the pinnacle of 90s JDM performance engineering.",
